Comment: a nice quick clash. Good suggestion.

I very love it. 
instead of solve this with brute force all number between 1 and N. it might work with only number between 1  and Math.sqrt(N).  this will reduce the complexity.  (à confirmer)
 
I very like this puzzle. thank you for sharing.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It is a simple and understandable problem, that will show if someone has grasped the basics of the language they're using relatively quickly.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Nice puzzle. Not difficult, can be definitely solved in 5 minutes. It has two solutions brute-force (check all possibilities and return the best one) and smart (check just one, correct possibility and return it)

Thank you for comments and rating!!
Now, the voting period is now open. If you like, please help us approve the puzzle.

Nice clash it's has 2 parts; one part to find the "a" and "b" that N=a*b, i think it's difficult part and the other part is find the minimum of (b-a).

Good job

Statment is clear, testcases works fine. Well done.
Although there is the same or very similiar one in clash already.

Thank you for your reply.
Oh, really? Then we may not need this problem. Would it be wise to delete it?

I would NOT remove it. It is very good. I like the puzzle. as many others do. About duplication, I found the following in documentation: "CoC close duplicates are not forbidden" https://www.codingame.com/ playgrounds/40701/contribute---help/contribution-guidelines

I am a beginner, with two puzzles done. And I also have big doubts, if they are unique. But, AFAIK, there is no way to check this out.
